  "mixStrategy": "This Classical focus score in D Major at 75 BPM is built around a clear harmonic foundation with four complementary tracks occupying distinct frequency bands. The CELLO BASS (20-300Hz) anchors the harmony with sustained roots and fifths in the C2-C4 range, providing a warm, steady foundation using legato whole and half notes. The STRING ENSEMBLE CHORDS (300Hz-2kHz) fill the harmonic body in the C3-C5 range with close-voiced triads and seventh chords, sustaining through each harmony change with gentle swells. The PIANO MELODY (1-8kHz) carries a lyrical, singable theme in the C4-C6 range with balanced 2-bar antecedent-consequent phrases, emphasizing chord tones on strong beats with stepwise passing tones on weak beats. The FLUTE TEXTURE (3kHz+) adds shimmer and air in the C5-C7 range with sparse counter-melodic fragments that ornament the melody without competing. All four tracks lock to the same chord progression: Segment 1-2 (0-16s): I(D) \u2192 IV(G) \u2192 V(A) \u2192 I(D); Segment 3-6 (16-45s): I(D) \u2192 vi(Bm) \u2192 IV(G) \u2192 V(A), repeated with variation. Energy arc: bars 1-2 at 0.4 (gentle entry), bars 3-4 at 0.6, bars 5-8 at 0.7 (sustained plateau), bars 9-10 at 0.7, final bars easing to 0.5. Velocity stays in 45-75 range for focus-mode habituation. Rhythmic interlock: bass plays on beats 1 and 3, chords sustain across bars, melody weaves eighth-note and quarter-note motion between bass pulses, flute enters on off-beats with gentle ornaments. All chord changes are synchronized across every track.",
